cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper focuses on the analysis of visual cues used by neural networks for depth estimation from single images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also investigates the MonoDepth network's behavior, which is a deep learning model, making it likely to also fall under machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the influence of camera pose on depth estimation, which relates to robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper explores the network's ability to estimate depth towards arbitrary obstacles, which is a problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
